OPTOUT_Green:
Imagine you have to relocate to another town. After you move into your new flat, you receive a letter from the electric power supplier, GreenGrid. You are told that by moving into your new flat you became an GreenGrid customer: ‘GreenGrid is pleased to welcome you as a new customer. We are responsible for the basic electricity supply in this residential area. GreenGrid sells clean electricity, generated from renewable energy sources. Contribute to climate protection and environmental protection! Your monthly premium is $39’. You are kindly asked to fill in some personal data on an attached document, which you do. A couple of days later a contract is sent to you.



Some weeks later you find a flyer in you mailbox, advertising offers from the electric power supplier Twon: ‘Switch to Twon! Did you know that you can easily switch your electricity supplier? We offer low-priced electricity tariffs—you cannot beat our prices. Save money with Twon! Your monthly premium will be $32.'



What do you do?
